Minimal safe patch:

```ts
function parseLimit(value: number | null | undefined) {
  if (value == null) throw new Error('missing');
  if (value < 0) throw new Error('invalid');
  return Math.min(value, 100);
}
```

Regression tests:

```ts
expect(parseLimit(0)).toBe(0);
expect(() => parseLimit(null)).toThrow('missing');
expect(() => parseLimit(undefined)).toThrow('missing');
expect(() => parseLimit(-1)).toThrow('invalid');
expect(parseLimit(100)).toBe(100);
expect(parseLimit(101)).toBe(100);
expect(parseLimit(42)).toBe(42);
```

`value == null` intentionally matches only `null` and `undefined`. No finite-number or integer validation should be added without an additional requirement.
